### 1. Create a new Airport (POST)
# We do not send airportId because it is @GeneratedValue
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/airport
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "airportName": "Charles de Gaulle",
  "airportCountry": "France",
  "airportCity": "Paris"
}

### 2. Get All Airports (GET)
# Check if CDG was added to the list
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/airport

### 3. Get Airport by ID (GET)
# Assuming the first one created has ID 1.
# If you restarted your app, the ID counter might have reset or incremented.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/airport/1

### 4. Update Airport (PUT)
# Let's change the city to "Roissy" (more specific location)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/airport/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "airportName": "Charles de Gaulle",
  "airportCountry": "France",
  "airportCity": "Roissy-en-France"
}

### 5. Verify Update (GET)
# Check if the city is now "Roissy-en-France"
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/airport/1

### 6. Delete Airport (DELETE)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/airport/1

### 7. Verify Deletion (GET)
# Should return 404 Not Found
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/airport/1